Tekserve, New York&rsquo;s premiere Apple Authorized Service Provider is currently looking for people who have what it takes to become a Tekserve Visual Merchandising Specialist. Are you are the type of person who can&rsquo;t help but rave about the superiority of computer systems driven by Apple technology? Are you passionate about the newest technologies? &nbsp;Do your friends turn to you to when they have questions about what the next big thing will be? &nbsp;We may have a place for you! As a Visual Merchandising Specialist you will not only be responsible for creating and maintaining the look and feel of the sales floor, but deciding what the total customer experience is like.</p>
<p>
The Visual Merchandising Specialist creates the ambience of the retail floor. They create engaging, intriguing, distinctive displays. &nbsp;They own the look and feel of the store and help ensure that our sales team has the right environment to showcase the right products. giving our valued customers the most outstanding shopping experience possible.&nbsp;<span style="font-size: 12px;">They understand the importance of the flow of product once it leaves the stockroom. &nbsp;They understand the careful planning that is required to bring together the complete supply chain from product research to display.</span></p>
<p>
<strong>Principal Duties</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Support the Retail Management team with visual store merchandising</li>
<li>
Participate in creation of product guides</li>
<li>
Ensure price tags on all product are visible and correct</li>
<li>
Work with Merchandising Manager to create dynamic, engaging displays</li>
<li>
Implement planograms and floor stock moves</li>
<li>
Track sales of displayed products to help ensure the best product is highlighted</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Competencies and Experience</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
2+ years of retail visual merchandising experience</li>
<li>
Upbeat, creative and dynamic person</li>
<li>
Ability to work with minimal supervision</li>
<li>
Must be able to work on the OS X operating system and associated applications</li>
<li>
High School diploma or equivalent</li>
<li>
Hours will&nbsp;be mostly Monday thru Friday with some weekends and late nights, but<br />
NO OVERNIGHTS.</li>
</ul>
<p>
Openings are full time.&nbsp; This is an hourly position with benefits including health benefits, paid vacation, paid holidays, employee discounts, and definitley a fun and unique work environment. Compensation is commensurate with experience.</p>
<p>
Women and minority candidates are encouraged to apply.</p>
