			<description><![CDATA[<p>
We are looking for full time shipping help at Tekserve. The Shipping team member is tasked with processing packages with extreme attention to detail. Shipping team members coordinate direct carriers, inspect and prepare packages, drive the core of courier relationships, and are the final layer of security and quality control at Tekserve.&nbsp; Shipping validates and legitimizes the flow of product, is extremely detail-driven and enables Tekserve to provide what we promise. Shipping work is oftentimes physically demanding and is always detail-driven.</p>
<p>
<strong>Principal Duties</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Evaluating all shipments for completeness of details, condition, and quantity.</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Packing items, completing all data entry requirements, creating packaging details, obtaining tracking numbers, and arranging carrier and courier pick-ups on an ongoing basis.</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Ensuring the complete and accurate entry of record into the database, noting all information, cost, communication, and service details (SN#, Part#, # of Pkgs, Qty, Tracking, etc).</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Proactively managing the shipping queue, expediting orders as necessary, coordinating with the Stock Room and Configuration Teams as needed in order to honor delivery windows.</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Report and escalate issues to the Logistics Manager, Stock Manager, and Credit as needed.</span></li>
<li>
<span style="font-size: 12px;">Increasing productivity and value by becoming fully cross-trained in at least one more Logistics area.</span></li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong><span style="font-size: 12px;">Accountabilities</span></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Accountable for managing the shipping queue and priority based work load balancing</li>
<li>
Responsible for providing professional and courteous interactions with customers, service providers, and fellow employees alike.</li>
<li>
Responsible for acting as the final quality check for all items being shipped from Tekserve</li>
<li>
Responsible for the prompt and accurate recording highly detailed database entries</li>
<li>
Responsible for completing assigned special tasks and for being capable of readily adapting to system and/or workflow changes.&nbsp; &nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Competencies and Experience</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
3-5 years (intermediate) experience is required.</li>
<li>
A very high degree of attention to detail, communication, adaptability, reliability, and responsiveness to the direct supervisor are key.</li>
<li>
Familiar with and capable of maintaining safe workplace practices.</li>
<li>
Experience in a customer-facing role will prove be beneficial.</li>
<li>
Persons experienced and competent with various warehouse/materials handling, shipping, receiving, or order management technologies are preferred.Filemaker-Pro database, Shopkeeper, and experience doing inventory using barcode scanner technologies are important.</li>
<li>
Shifts in this department generally range from 8:00 am &ndash; 6:30 pm.</li>
<li>
A working fluency in English.</li>
<li>
You must be able to manage and lift 50+ lbs.</li>
<li>
Applicable work experience is highly valued, as are internal &amp; strong work references.</li>
<li>
Impeccable honesty is a must. (Background check and references required.)</li>
<li>
Knowledge of Apple Computers and Apple related products a plus.</li>
</ul>
<p>
Women and minority applicants are encouraged to apply.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
]]></description>
