			<description><![CDATA[<p>
The Sales Specialist is Tekserve&rsquo;s frontline for sales and customer service. They are the face of Tekserve and thus the key to our success. They carry&nbsp; on the tradition of exceptional customer service, superior product knowledge and sales skills. Sales Specialists main goal is to delight our customers&ndash;to go above and beyond to solve our customer&rsquo;s IT needs and bring them new, useful and interesting products. They also collect our customer&rsquo;s product needs and ideas and feedback to Managers and Product Managers. Sales Specialists are awake, curious, active, and friendly. They treat customer&rsquo;s and coworkers with the highest respect and search out new ways to improve Tekserve&rsquo;s systems to make Tekserve a more profitable and unique business.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Principal Duties</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<strong>Customer Service</strong>: Specialists have impeccable ability to charm, understand and to properly outfit our customers with electronic gear. A Specialist must have strong social skills to communicate with our very diverse customers. They have the ability to convert upset customers and the gregariousness to connect with new clients.</li>
<li>
<strong>Product Knowledge</strong>: Specialists have a deep knowledge and interest in the latest electronic gear, especially Apple products. They keep up with blogs and publications to stay at the cutting edge of technology and use and experiment with the latest tech products. They train at Tekserve as well as train themselves to be the goto guy for emerging tech and products.</li>
<li>
<strong>Tech Knowledge</strong>: Specialists keep up with emerging trends in technology. They read tech blogs and publications daily as well as the Apple website and Apple-specific blogs. They have a strong understanding and interest in electronics, software, and hardware from headphones to pro applications.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Accountabilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<strong>Customer Service</strong>: Specialists are rated on their ability to proactively charm customers and solve their tech needs. They need to be actively seeking out customers for sales and connections.</li>
<li>
<strong>Productivity</strong>: Specialists are accountable for the number of SROs per hour and Margin per hour.</li>
<li>
<strong>Items per SRO</strong>: Specialist are accountable for the number of line items per SRO.</li>
<li>
<strong>Customer Feedback</strong>: Specialist receive feedback from Customer Surveys and need to adjust behavior based on our customer&rsquo;s perceptions.</li>
<li>
<strong>Certification</strong>: Apple Sales Training Online = 12000 points </li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Experience</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
2-3 years in a Retail environment (preferably electronics)</li>
<li>
High School Diploma or GED required</li>
<li>
Able to work a dynamic schedule up to 40 hours and including nights and weekends</li>
<li>
Ability to lift up to 50 pounds and be on your feet for 8+ hours a day</li>
</ul>
